Job Description:
Job Overview

Business Analyst – Cisco FACT




Responsibilities and Duties

Responsibilities:

Supports business processes and workflow;
Identifies any associated issues and risks;
Monitors performance and results;
Is responsible for addressing performance issues and creating action plans for improvement;
Oversees database management;
Performs data and application maintenance updates;
Escalates database issues and acts as a first POC for escalations;
Communicates with internal stakeholders and vendors;
Identifies, escalates data and program specific issues to appropriate level of management;
Proactively identifies internal and external best practices that will enable improvement of the standard end-to-end process;
Generates reports and analyses client/vendor reports;
Consistently meets or exceeds OPT’s key performance standards and quality objectives;
Other Ad-hoc duties.

Qualifications:

At least 6 months experience in the current team;
Not in an Active Correction Plan or Process Improvement Plan;
Fluency in English;
Very good verbal, written and interpersonal communication skills;
Experience in relationship management with customers/vendors;
Ability to perform duties with minimum direction;
Ability to work in a team environment;
Ability to receive feedback and handle high pressure situations;
Continuous attention to detail and quality;
Very good Excel knowledge – e.g., XLOOKUP, Conditional formatting, Pivot tables, Chart and Dashboard creation;
Experience with Tableu is an advantage;
Good presentation skills;
Great understanding of supply chain E2E process;
Strong work ethics – capable of handling confidential information.
Experience with Power BI would be considered an advantage



Education Requirements

High School or equivalent




Experience Requirements

Less than 1 year




About OnProcess

OnProcess is on a mission – to transform and drive the world’s circular service supply chains – for brilliant customer experiences, efficiencies at the speed of digital, and more sustainable ‘circular economy’ processes.
At OnProcess, we encourage a collective sense of engagement, affirmation and belonging, where everyone is proud to be a member of our company. As a global business, we recognize our ability to understand, embrace and operate in a multicultural world – both in the marketplace and in the workplace – is critical to our long-term sustainability. That’s why we are committed to a company-wide culture that understands that diversity, equity, and inclusion is essential.

DUTIES:

Gather requirements from the business, articulate on what the business needs, translate the information into comprehensive functional and technical design, and coordinate with the Group or Division IT and IT Shared Services Team to deliver the solution;

Work with business and IT through the entire Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC), i.e., requirement and gap analysis, design process mapping, testing scripting development and testing, deployment, and postproduction;

Collect and understand the business overall goals, requirements, and objectives, assisting in prioritization of business technology projects, ensuring that projects align with the technology that best provides maximum return on investment, and linking IT strategy in support of the overall business and service line strategy;

Serve as the liaison between the business, Group/Division IT, and IT Shared Services for the technology need and act as an advocate for the business;

Work with business area end users to build out knowledge of SAP best practices in the end-user community;

Identify innovative technical and process solutions that drive the desired performance in cost, quality, compliance, customer service, and revenue;

Ensure that teams are adhering to and supporting quality procedures and policies;

Assist in IT architecture, strategy, and roadmap planning;

Plan, organize, and execute on various focus groups and initiatives to drive process improvements across the organization.

REQUIREMENTS: Bachelor’s degree or foreign degree equivalent in Engineering (any), Computer Science, or related field of study plus 5 years of experience in computer applications management working with SAP, or related experience. Employer will also accept a Master’s degree or foreign degree equivalent in Engineering (any), Computer Science, or related field of study plus 3 years of experience in computer applications management with SAP, or related experience as an equivalent alternative.

Must have experience or knowledge of:

Experience in the pharmaceutical or life sciences industry;

Supply chain business processes, including materials planning and MRP processes, material scheduling, receipts, inspections and warehousing operations;

SAP software implementation experience;

SAP supply chain focused modules, including Materials Management, Production Planning, Quality Management and warehouse management;

Experience working in validated environments that meet 21 CFR part 11;

Experience translating technical requirements into business requirements and vice versa; and

Identifying organizational change impacts to current processes or procedures and identifying impacted users for changes being proposed to the SAP system.

Travel: Willing to travel up to 15% domestic and international. Telecommuting Employee: Reports to company headquarters in Waltham, MA. Can work remotely or telecommute.

Job Description

DUTIES:

Work with Site Leadership to identify and address areas of process improvement.

Drive cataloging of opportunities, quantification of opportunities, management of resources to capture data, coordination of ideation and project management to ensure execution of achievements. Consolidate and analyze global inventory data for trends and reduction opportunities.

Establish and standardize global demand data for monthly operations reviews.

Conduct analysis across all CAD Business Units to find and lead SKU rationalization initiatives.

Collaborate across functions to ensure consistent implementation of new, improved processes.

Establish measurable criteria to ensure desired results are acquired and provide management with updates via tracking reports reflective of Key Performance Indicators in line with set priorities and timing targets.

Identify training needs for the facilities and assist in the deployment of agreed to training techniques, content, and timing.

Promote the transformation of a reactive organizational culture to one that is more proactive, utilizing data driven decision-making, and giving priority to preventative actions.

Train and educate the organization and to implement continuous improvement methodologies including PPI, 6 Sigma, 5S, Lean, OEE and others.

Review business process to improve efficiency and benchmark with industry Best Practices.

REQUIREMENTS:Bachelor’s degree in Industrial Engineering, Manufacturing, or related field of study plus 2 years of experience as a Manufacturing Engineer, PPI Specialist, or any related occupation in which the required experience can be gained.

Must have experience or knowledge of:

RCCMs, PPI, Six Sigma, 5S, Lean, OEE, and other Continuous Improvement techniques and their application;

Sig Sigma Green Belt training;

DMAIC principles: Define, Measure, Analyze, Improve, Control;

Leading programs/projects and managing teams in a manufacturing environment;

Applied statistical models/engines;

Electronics, X-ray tube manufacturing or bench top manufacturing;

ERP systems (Infor XA, Intuitive, ABAS, or SAP) and MRP processes;

Product sourcing, supply chain improvement, and delivery execution;

Material flow through manufacturing sites and production/capacity planning.

Travel: Roving/Telecommuting Employee: Reports to company headquarters in Waltham, MA. Will work at various unknown client sites throughout the U.S. for up to 70% of the time. Must be willing to travel anywhere in the U.S. and may be assigned to work at client sites across the U.S. Can work remotely or telecommute.

Who We Are:
Yesway is one of the fastest-growing convenience store operators in the United States. Established in 2015, Yesway is a multi-branded platform headquartered in Fort Worth, Texas, which operates 403 stores located in Texas, New Mexico, South Dakota, Iowa, Kansas, Missouri, Wyoming, Oklahoma, and Nebraska. We operate our portfolio primarily under two successful brands, Yesway and Allsup’s. Our sites are differentiated through a leading foodservice offering, featuring Allsup’s famous deep-fried burrito, and a wide variety of high-quality grocery items and private-label products. Our geographic footprint consists of stores located in attractive rural and suburban markets across the Midwest and Southwest, where we often are the convenience retail destination of choice and effectively the local grocer. We have a successful track record of growing through acquisitions and believe we are well positioned to continue to solidify our market position and grow our store count. We have received numerous industry awards for our growth initiatives, management team, loyalty program, and our employees’ contributions to the industry. We offer competitive wages and outstanding benefits. Yesway values employees who thrive in a fast-paced, service-oriented, work culture and are focused on execution and collaboration.
The Opportunity:
Yesway is seeking a Financial Reporting and Data Analyst within our gas station and convenience store business. We are looking for a candidate who has employee relations and change management experience, is excited to join our team and is passionate about taking a role in a rapidly-growing company.
Position Responsibilities:
Analyzes financial results by collecting, monitoring, and studying data; recommending actions;
Prepares budget-to-actual variance analysis for review and dissemination to senior management;
Develops/modify reports for operations and finance based on changing business needs;
Prepares monthly and quarterly general lender reporting schedules and analysis;
Guides cost analysis process by establishing and enforcing policies and procedures; providing trends and forecasts; explaining processes and techniques; recommending actions;
Improves financial status by analyzing results; monitoring variances; identifying trends; recommending actions to management;
Reconciles transactions and recommends actions by analyzing and interpreting data as well as conducting comparative analyses and correcting data as needed;
Researches industry trends and best practices; makes recommendations for enhanced reporting.
Requirements:
Bachelor's degree in accounting, finance, business, data analytics, or related field;
2+ years of previous financial data analysis experience required;
Experience analyzing from a large pool of data and the ability to manage large volumes of transactions;
Demonstrated strong analytical skills and attention to detail;
Excellent interpersonal, verbal and written communication skills;
Ability to manage multiple tasks and meet demanding deadlines;
Expert knowledge of Microsoft Excel. (Index-Match, Indirect, Offset, SUMIFS, SUMPRODUCT, Array Formulas, VBA); and
Excellent problem solving skills and self-motivated learning abilities.
Preferred Skills:
Strong statistics background (specifically in generalized linear modeling)
Intermediate to advanced knowledge of an object-oriented programming language (Python, Java, C++);
Experience with a data-focused programming language (R, Python, SAS);
Experience with machine-learning techniques;
Experience building advanced financial models and Monte-Carlo simulations; and
Experience with T-SQL and SSRS preferred

PURPOSE AND SCOPE:

Support the processing of payroll for all U.S. employees. The position is responsible for analyses of payroll systems to identify potential issues and optimize the efficiency and efforts of the Payroll Operations department; performance of complex payroll tasks, and will serve as a subject matter expert on relevant systems.



PRINCIPAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES:

Ensure the Workday payroll system is setup with all necessary parameters and definitions in order to process all on-cycle and off-cycle payrolls in accordance with business requirements;
Act as an active member for the Workday community - staying ahead of Workday updates, fixes and resolution;
Review and assess new system functionality / upgrades to determine relevance to current business processes and make recommendation as to whether enhancements should be implemented in the system;
Lead the planning and execution of payroll test scenarios and test scripts prior to system change being deployed to the production environment, validating that the outcome meets business expectations ;
Perform analysis of existing business processes design and identify possible re-configuration/solutions in response to business issues and challenges; work with payroll leadership to evaluate and prioritize;
Serve as a payroll liaison when working with cross-functional business teams to translate complex business needs to effective design recommendations;
Serve as the key contact to work with IT to discuss and coordinate any enhancements requiring their support;
Act as the subject matter expert and provide help desk type support to all payroll personnel for questions about Workday functionality;
Manage and respond to various reporting needs, including the assessment of existing reports, accuracy of data on them, and appropriate security access to the reports;
Responsible for functional system-level setup activities such as setting up new earnings, deductions, and special payroll runs;
Responsible for mass uploads into the payroll system (i.e. wage garnishment files, bonus files);
Other activities include job scheduling and execution; ongoing system maintenance; development and updating of process documentation; and providing user training;
Other duties as assigned;

